## Get User

```
GET /api/users/{id}
```

This endpoint retrieves a user.

#### Parameters

`id` - user identifier

#### Response

```
{
  "id": "123",
  "name": "john doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}
```

## Create User

```
POST /api/users
```

Creates a new user in the system.

##### Request Body

```json
{
  "name": "string",
  "email": "string"
}
```

## Delete User

```
DELETE /api/users/{id}
```

This endpoint is used for deleting users from the system. The deletion is permanent and cannot be undone.

###### Response

200 OK - user deleted
404 Not Found - user not found

## List Users

Endpoint: `/api/users`
Method: GET

Returns all users. [Click here](https://docs.example.com/api/users) for more info.

Response:
```
[
  { "id": "1", "name": "user1" },
  { "id": "2", "name": "user2" }
]
```

## Common Errors

The API may return errors. Here are the common ones:

- 400 - Bad Request
- 401 - unauthorized
- 403 - Forbidden
- 404 - not found
- 500 - Server Error
